n and documentation to track and fix bugs. Some platforms allow you to log bug reports via email, and others automatically detect and report issues. Also, some platforms automatically detect and merge duplicate bugs so your team doesnÂ t waste time on multiple reports. Consider what bug-reporting features benefit your software development team when looking at software options.","<strong>Team Management</strong><br/>Your team needs a dashboard that displays bug and issue reports in a clear, functional way. Look for dashboards that allow team members to filter them in terms of what issues they&#39;re assigned to help prioritize tasks. Dashboards with advanced search functions allow you to search the entire body of a bug report to identify and link common issues. Finally, dashboards help administrators evaluate the workflow of individual team members so tasks are assigned accordingly. That also helps to monitor project milestones.","<strong>Team Communication</strong><br/>Some software development teams keep track of bugs in spreadsheets and email chains. Look for bug tracking software that eliminates that step. Team members should be able to upload notes, screenshots, documents or videos directly into bug report fields. They should also be able to see who completed tasks by simply opening a ticket. Also, look for an application that sends automatic notifications to groups of users once specific tasks are completed, or that emails regular progress reports to team members.","<strong>Price Plans</strong><br/>Bug tracking software offers flexible price points for development teams of all sizes. Open-source bug tracking tools are free of charge, but third-party plugins may require an additional charge. Other platforms charge monthly rates based on the number of active users or active projects your team has. Look for a tiered pricing system that allows the platform to grow and contract with your team&#39;s current needs. Many platforms offer flexible price points to accomplish that.","Bug tracking software can help you identify and resolve issues at every stage of the development process. It allows your team to visualize workflow, progress and individual tasks. Ultimately, it helps your team ship quality software on time."]},"id":"85de1dc2-6270-406d-8c06-ef6bce7a00ad","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Related Product Reviews"},"id":"4c07db75-c915-442c-a586-305e78f138f6","type":"heading"},{"data":{"items":["<a href=\"http://www.axosoft.com/bug-tracker\">Axosoft</a>","<a href=\"https://www.bontq.com/\">Bontq</a>","<a href=\"https://www.bugzilla.org/download/#howtoget\">Bugzilla</a>","<a href=\"https://www.getdonedone.com/plans-pricing/\">DoneDone</a>","<a href=\"https://www.fogcreek.com/fogbugz/pricing/\">Fog Creek Software</a>","<a href=\"https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira\">Jira</a>","<a href=\"https://lighthouseapp.com/plans\">Lighthouse Entp</a>","<a href=\"http://www.mantisbt.org/\">MantisBT</a>","<a href=\"https://sifterapp.com/about/pricing/\">Next Update</a>","<a href=\"https://www.zoho.com/projects/zohoprojects-pricing.html\">Zoho</a>"],"type":"ul"},"id":"59e80594-046f-4dcc-be0a-0af260b10677","type":"list"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"comparison_page_1814","url":"/best-bug-tracking-software","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"top-ten-reviews-staff","url":"/author/top-ten-reviews-staff","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Top Ten Reviews Staff","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"EcXXb3s8QKwvex3rQshgX5","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2015-06-02T21:42:48Z","datePublished":"2015-09-15T22:06:31Z","name":"Bug Tracking Software Review","synopsis":"Software development teams use bug tracking software platforms to report, track and fix bugs, and team leaders use it to manage workflow and ensure software versions ship on time.","review":{},"strapline":"Software development teams use bug tracking software platforms to report, track and fix bugs, and team 